Permissions Commands

Linux me har file ke 3 tarah ke permissions hote hain:
- Read (r)
- Write (w)
- Execute (x)

Aur ye 3 users ke liye apply hote hain:
- Owner
- Group
- Others

chmod → File permissions change karta hai
chown → File ka owner ya group change karta hai

Examples:
ls -l
chmod 755 script.sh
chmod u+x script.sh
chown user1 file.txt
chown user1:group1 file.txt

